Summary: This section introduces occlusion culling in 3D rendering, outlining its purpose and the topics covered in the tutorial.
Occlusion culling is the process of performing hidden geometry removal in a 3D rendering engine. This tutorial will cover the advantages and pitfalls of occlusion culling, how to set it up in Godot, and troubleshooting common issues.
